Program: Outlook
Title: 29/03/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00q86nq
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 30 Mar 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Natasha Owen Jones, the British woman who spent 20 years looking for her adopted brother, only to discover he was in jail for murder. And, after the recent siege in Toulouse, Outlook talks to Christophe Caupenne, a French police commander who's been involved in 350 sieges, about the art of negotiation. And finally, we meet Anthony Mancinelli who at the age of 101, is the world's oldest barber - still cutting New Yorkers' hair. Show less